OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,403,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F402A1774001116
OL,3,CSadiq Khan: Labour should pledge to
OL,4,Crejoin the EU at next election
OL,6,FNo 10 sought to pour cold water on the
OL,7,Fidea, saying Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,8,FGovernment would be sticking to its
OL,9,Fred lines as it deepens ties with the
OL,10,FEU.
OL,12,FThe Prime Minister's official
OL,13,Fspokesman said: "We will not be
OL,14,Frejoining the customs union, the
OL,15,Fsingle market or returning to freedom
OL,16,Fof movement.
OL,18,F"Those are our red lines as per the
OL,19,FGovernment's manifesto.
OL,26,@uD@QOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/7
